Installation and execution:

1. Download Eclipse Modeling Tools (Eclipse 4.4.1 Luna).
    * https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/
2. Install AJDT (which is needed for AspectJ).
    * In Eclipse: go Help -> Install new software and type http://download.eclipse.org/tools/ajdt/44/dev/update
    * Installing only the first (required) component should work.
3. Restart Eclipse.
4. Import the project into the workspace (does not need to be copied inside the workspace).
5. Run as AspectJ/Java application.